laboratory_examinations.findings: The distal appendix is dilated, measuring up to 12 mm with a 7 mm obstructing appendicolith noted in the lumen and surrounding fat stranding and peritoneal thickening in the right paracolic gutter, but no evidence of free air or abscess formation. Other findings show no abnormality in the lungs, liver, gallbladder, pancreas, spleen, adrenals, kidneys, gastrointestinal tract, or pelvis.
